cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) tasks, specifically age progression and regression. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework based on conditional Generative Adversarial Networks (cGANs), which falls under the category of machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The use of spatial attention mechanisms to limit image modifications is related to multimedia (MM) and human-computer interaction (HC), making cs.MM and cs.HC possible sub-categories as well.
